title: Daniel Murphy and Jeurys Familia celebrating the final out in the Mets victor... - NorthJersey.com
text:
The fault line ripped open when David Wright's heretofore silent bat awoke with a scorching double to center field, a deep Citi Field hit that would give the Mets the first run in the first inning of this pivotal second game of the National League Championship Series against the Cubs. The earthquake of noise continued as Wright cruised into second base and Curtis Granderson crossed home plate - yet another sold-out home crowd dancing to the marvelous sounds of postseason baseball, their long-suffering wait for a night like this more than enough protection against the cold Queens air.
 NorthJersey.com.
